<div class="col-md-3">
  <br>
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">
  <div class="panel panel-body center">
    <h2>ToyBot Simulator &nbsp;<a class="btn btn-default" href="#popup1">?</a></h2>
    <hr>
    <%= form_for(@robot, url: command_robots_path) do |f| %>

    <%= f.text_field :x_coordinate, placeholder: 'X-coordinate' %>
    <%= f.text_field :y_coordinate, placeholder: 'Y-coordinate' %>
    <%= f.text_field :facing, placeholder: 'Direction' %>
    <br><br>
    <%= f.submit 'Place', class: "btn btn-default" %>

    <br><hr><br>

    <%= label_tag ("Commands: ") %><br>
    <%= f.radio_button :command, "MOVE" %>
    <%= label_tag("MOVE") %>
    <%= f.radio_button :command, "LEFT" %>
    <%= label_tag("LEFT") %>
    <%= f.radio_button :command, "RIGHT" %>
    <%= label_tag("RIGHT") %>
    <%= f.radio_button :command, "REPORT" %>
    <%= label_tag("REPORT") %>
    <br><br>
    <%= f.submit 'Okay', class: "btn btn-default" %>

    <br><hr><br>

    <% end %>


    </div>
  </div>


</div>

<div class="col-md-3">
  <br>
</div>

<div id="popup1" class="overlay">
    <div class="popup">
        <h3>ToyBot Rules:</h3>
        <a class="close" href="#">&times;</a>
        <div class="content">
          <ol>
            <li>The application is a simulation of a toy robot moving on a square tabletop, of dimensions 5 units x 5 units. </li>
            <li>There are no other obstructions on the table surface. </li>
            <li>The robot is free to roam around the surface of the table, but is prevented from falling down of the table. </li>
            <li>PLACE will put the toy robot on the table in position X, Y and facing NORTH, SOUTH, EAST or WEST. </li>
            <li>The origin (0,0) can be considered to be the SOUTH WEST most corner. </li>
            <li>The first valid command to the robot is a PLACE command, after that, any sequence of commands may be issued, in any order, including another PLACE command. </li>
            <li>MOVE will move the toy robot one unit forward in the direction it is currently facing. </li>
            <li>LEFT and RIGHT will rotate the robot 90 degrees in the specified direction without changing the position of the robot. </li>
            <li>REPORT will announce the X, Y and F of the robot. </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
